XVIII. ou tuoruum PARENTIUM cursen.

Exemplo patronorum recepta est et alia tutela, quae et ipsa legitima vocatur. nam si quis filium aut filiam, nepotem aut neptem ex lilio et deinceps impuberes emancipaverit, legitimus eorum tutor erit.

'stt XVII Where a libertus civis died intestate, having no suus heres (the meaning ol intestati in the text), the patron took his property as (by a fiction) his nearest agnate, and the tutela went in the same way on the analogy ol the legitima adgnatorum tutela. But when a Latinus lunianus (who could neither have a suus heres nor make a will) died, the patron took the property bya different title, iure peculii (Blc iii. 7. itini). Hence the succession ol the tutela did not necessarily go together: ‘unde s'i ancilla ex iure Quiritium tua sit, in bonis mea, a me quidem solo, non etiarn ate manumissa, Latina fieri potest, et bona eius ad me pertinent, sed eius tutela tibi competit: nam ita lege iulia cavetur' Gaius i. 167.
